Vol / Page:  88
Edition:
Quote:  <i>POMADERRIS APETALA, tainui</i>. An erect, rather narrow shrub growing to 5m tall. ... Known as a wild plant only in a few North Island sites, it is widespread in Tasmania and nearby parts of mainland Australia.
